to add css styles to the homepage, you can create a new CSS file in your static directory and link it in your HTML template. Here's how you can do it:
1. Create a new CSS file in your static directory, for example, `static/css/homepage.css`.
2. Add your CSS styles to this file.
3. In your HTML template for the homepage, link the CSS file in the `<head>` section like this:
```html     
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="{% static 'css/homepage.css' %}">
4. Make sure you have the `{% load static %}` tag at the top of your HTML template to use the static files.
5. Now, you can add your CSS styles in the `homepage.css` file, and they will be applied to the homepage.
This will allow you to style your homepage with custom CSS. Make sure to run the Django development server to see the changes reflected in your browser.                        





